author: andreasmyth
msg: Fixed problems with WSDL genenation using tools from JAXWS RI and removed inconsistent usages of logging.
All java.util.logging.Logger references are static final, named LOG, and all classes use their own Logger.

WSDL is generated by running WsGen in a forked VM and then collecting the results (com.sun.tools.ws.WsGen performs a System.exit, and com.sun.tools.ws.ant.WsGen speears to be have bugs).  Note that the generated WSDL is incomplete (lacks binding and address information).
Package org.objectweb.celtix.common.command has been added to support this.
Fixed test target to use the correct logging properties file in unit/system tests.
